# Super Admin Coding Conventions

This document outlines the coding conventions and patterns used in the Super Admin section of the application.

## Naming Conventions

- Component names should be prefixed with `SuperAdmin` followed by their purpose, e.g., `SuperAdminTable`, `SuperAdminPagination`
- File and directory names in the `src/components/SuperAdmin` directory should use PascalCase
- Page components in `src/app/(super-admin)/super-admin/*` should use standard Next.js conventions with `page.tsx` for page components

## Component Structure

- Components should be kept under 150 lines of code for maintainability
- Reusable UI components should be placed in `src/components/SuperAdmin`
- Page-specific components should be co-located with their pages in `src/app/(super-admin)/super-admin/*`

## Data Fetching and State Management

- API service functions for Super Admin operations are in [src/services/super-admin](mdc:src/services/super-admin)
- Type definitions for Super Admin related data are in [src/types/super-admin](mdc:src/types/super-admin)
- Recoil atoms for state management are in [src/atoms/super-admin](mdc:src/atoms/super-admin)

## Layout and UI

- All pages should use the main Super Admin layout defined in [src/app/(super-admin)/layout.tsx](mdc:src/app/(super-admin)/layout.tsx)
- Table components should use the standardized [SuperAdminTable](mdc:src/components/SuperAdmin/Table/index.tsx) component
- Mobile responsiveness is handled through specific Mobile components and conditional rendering based on screen size

## Common Patterns

### Tables and Data Display

Tables should follow this pattern:
```tsx
<SuperAdminTable
  data={data}
  columns={columns}
  pagination={pagination}
  filterComponent={<FilterComponent />}
/>
```

### Page Structure

Super Admin pages typically follow this structure:
```tsx
export default function SomeSuperAdminPage() {
  return (
    <SuperAdminLayoutContentWrapper
      title="Page Title"
      description="Page description"
      actionButtons={<ActionButtons />}
    >
      {/* Page content */}
    </SuperAdminLayoutContentWrapper>
  );
}
```

